175 Facts About NYU                                              Bust of Sylvette The sculpture that adorns the courtyard     of NYU's Silver Towers apartment buildings on Bleecker Street is an     enlargement of a sculpture by Picasso. Norweigan sculptor Carl Nesjär     executed the construction of the 60-ton concrete Bust of Sylvette     in 1967.                  <    Previous    Next    >
